Edition:
Quote: It would be more appropriate if the laundry whistle was blown when Wairoa geyser was soaped.
Notes:

Date: 12/5/1903
Source: Hawera & Normanby Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: Complaint is made by a correspondent of the Hot Lakes Chronicle against  the indiscriminate soaping of the great Wairoa Geyser. The correspondent asserts that, in spite of the well-known fact that the geysers of Yellowstone Park, U.S.A., were almost ruined by too frequently soaping them, the authorities at Rotorua permit the great Wairoa Geyser to be soaped so frequently that from playing from an hour to an hour and a half it has deteriorated into a short action of a few minutes.
